RAF Watch

Map of UK military aircraft flights using ADS-B data.

Hex codes are scraped from live-mobile-mode-s.eu. Flight traces
are fetched from globe.adsbexchange.com (tar1090 format) and
stored as binary containers, parsed client-side. The frontend is
static HTML/CSS/JS with MapLibre GL.

Setup

  uv run scrape_hex.py             Scrape hex codes
  uv run fetch.py                  Fetch last 14 days of traces
  uv run fetch.py --days 7         Fetch last 7 days
  python -m http.server            Serve and open localhost:8000

The fetch script caches results in data/cache/ and is resumable.
Each day's data is stored as a separate .bin file loaded on demand
by the date slider.

Binary format (per-day .bin files)

  [uint32 LE]  entry count
  per entry:
    [uint32 LE]  ICAO hex code as integer
    [uint32 LE]  byte length of JSON payload
    [N bytes]    raw JSON response from adsbexchange

Data sources

  Hex codes    https://live-mobile-mode-s.eu/overviewall.php?DGCountry=UK
  Traces       https://globe.adsbexchange.com/globe_history/
